'''Albert Perera''' (died 1965) was a former Sri Lankan male boxer who mainly competed in the bantamweight category.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.olympic.org/albert-perera|title=Albert PERERA - Olympic Boxing {{!}} Sri Lanka|date=2016-06-16|work=International Olympic Committee|access-date=2018-02-04|language=en}}</ref> 

==Career==
He represented [[Ceylon at the 1948 Summer Olympics]], the year Ceylon got independence  from the British Empire. It was also the first Olympics where Ceylon was eligible to participate and Albert competed in the [[Boxing at the 1948 Summer Olympics – Men's bantamweight|men's bantamweight]] event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pe/albert-perera-1.html|title=Albert Perera Bio, Stats, and Results|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1948/BOX/mens-bantamweight.html|title=Boxing at the 1948 London Summer Games: Men's Bantamweight|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.island.lk/2008/07/22/sports5.html|title=The Island-Sports|website=www.island.lk|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.olympiandatabase.com/index.php?id=86972&L=1|title=Albert Perera - Olympic Facts and Results|last=Sportsencyclo|website=www.olympiandatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref> Albert Perera also represented [[Ceylon]] at the [[1950 British Empire Games]] and clinched a silver medal in the [[1950 British Empire Games#Boxing|men's bantamweight category]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.island.lk/2002/07/07/sports04.html|title=sports04|website=www.island.lk|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref>

