{{BLP sources|date=November 2015}} {{Infobox boxer | name = Jorge Sebastian Heiland | realname = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | nickname = ''El Gaucho de Pigüé'' | weight = [[Middleweight]] | height = | reach = | nationality = Argentine | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1987|02|05|}} | birth_place = [[Cipolletti]], [[Río Negro Province|Rio Negro]], Argentina | style = [[Southpaw stance|Southpaw]] | total = 36 | wins = 29 | KO = 16 | losses = 5 | draws = 2 | no contests = 0 }}
'''Jorge Sebastian Heiland''' (born 5 February 1987) is an Argentine [[professional boxer]] and the current [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] International [[middleweight]] champion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxrec.com/boxer/389007|title=BoxRec - Jorge Sebastian Heiland|work=boxrec.com}}</ref>
==Professional boxing== He made his debut in 2007, defeating Ceferino Juan Jose Coronel by UD decision. In 2009, Heiland won vacant [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] Latino [[Middleweight]] title, defeating Gaston Alejandro Vega.
On November 29, 2013, he won the vacant [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] International [[Middleweight]] title, defeating Billi Facundo Godoy.
