==Micro-history==
It was thought by some that Alexander was involved in the murder as he hoped to marry the marginally younger and more attractive Mary, however given their respective ages this seems unlikely given average lifespan at the time.{{sfn|Love|2003|p=30}} At the time it was certainly unusual for an attractive woman to remain unmarried and to live with her sister and brother-in-law for so many years.

The author Jack House described the murder in his book ''Murder Not Proven''.{{sfn|Hodgkinson|2002|p=111}}

Postcards were sold showing Northbank Cottage with a policeman standing on guard duty outside{{sfn|Hodgkinson|2002|p=111}} and sold in thousands.

Mary was the granddaughter of Margaret Gibson Spier who established [[Spier's school]] at Beith.

