[[File:Portrait of Mustapha Aga Emissary to the Swedish Court.jpg|thumb|Portrait of Mustapha Aga, emissary to the Swedish Court, 1727. [[George Engelhardt Schroeder]] (1684-1750).]] [[File:George Engelhardt Schröder - Kozbekçi Mustafa Ağa and his Retinue - Google Art Project.jpg|thumb|Kozbekçi Mustafa Ağa and his Retinue]] '''Kozbekçi Mustafa Ağa''', known as '''Mustapha Aga''' in Sweden, was an [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] ambassador to the [[Sweden|Swedish]] court in 1727. One of his missions was to obtain a repayment of a royal debt which had been incurred by [[Charles XII of Sweden]], but he failed in his mission.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=3ndGhM-lAZQC&pg=PA53 Imber, p.53]</ref> He was painted smoking [[nargile]] by [[George Engelhardt Schroeder]] (1684–1750).<ref name="Imber, p.53">Imber, p.53</ref>
He was succeeded by [[Yirmisekizzade Mehmed Said Pasha|Yirmisekizzade Mehmed Said Efendi]] in his role as ambassador.<ref name="Imber, p.53"/>
