'''Novel virus''' refers to a virus not seen before. It can be a virus that is isolated from its reservoir or isolated as the result of spread to an animal or human host where the virus had not been identified before. It can be an emergent virus, one that represents a new strain, but it can also be an extant virus not previously identified.<ref>Strauss, James H. ''Viruses and Human Disease''. San Diego. Academic Press. 2002.</ref><ref>Horowitz, Leonard G. ''Emerging Viruses: AIDS and Ebola: Nature, Accident or Intentional?'' Healthy World Distributor. April 1996.</ref>
