{{other people|James Colquhoun}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}
{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}
'''Sir James Colquhoun, 4th Baronet, of Luss''' (7 February 1804 &ndash; 18 December 1873) was the [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) for [[Dunbartonshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Dumbartonshire]] from  1837 to 1841.<ref>{{Rayment-hc|d|4|date=April 2015}}</ref> He drowned in 1873 when he and others rowed out to bring back a deer for a Christmas feast. He and all aboard the boat were lost off [[Inch Lonaig]] during a sudden storm. In his memory his son, also James, had the church rebuilt.<ref>[http://www.clancolquhoun.com/clan-history?start=2 History of the Colquhouns], Clan Colquhoun, retrieved 20 April 2015</ref>

